comment:
* Class stores information related to NR network VoPS support
 * @hide

variables.name: NR_STATUS_VOPS_NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * Indicates network does not support vops

variables.name: NR_STATUS_VOPS_3GPP_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * Indicates network supports vops over 3gpp access.

variables.name: NR_STATUS_VOPS_NON_3GPP_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * Indicates network supports vops over non 3gpp access

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMC_NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * Indicates network does not support emergency service

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMC_5GCN_ONLY
variables.comment: * Indicates network supports emergency service in NR connected to 5GCN only

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMC_EUTRA_5GCN_ONLY
variables.comment: * Indicates network supports emergency service in E-UTRA connected to 5GCN only

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMC_NR_EUTRA_5GCN
variables.comment:
* Indicates network supports emergency service in NR connected to 5GCN and
     * E-UTRA connected to 5GCN

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMF_NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * Indicates network does not support emergency service

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMF_5GCN_ONLY
variables.comment: * Indicates network supports emergency service fallback in NR connected to 5GCN only

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMF_EUTRA_5GCN_ONLY
variables.comment: * Indicates network supports emergency service fallback in E-UTRA connected to 5GCN only

variables.name: NR_STATUS_EMF_NR_EUTRA_5GCN
variables.comment:
* Indicates network supports emergency service fallback in NR connected to 5GCN
     * and E-UTRA connected to 5GCN

methods.name: public int getVopsSupport()
methods.comment:
* Provides the NR VoPS support capability as described in:
     * 3GPP 24.501 EPS network feature support -> IMS VoPS

methods.name: public int getEmcSupport()
methods.comment:
* Provides the NR Emergency bearer support capability as described in:
     * 3GPP 24.501 EPS network feature support -> EMC, and
     * 38.331 SIB1 : ims-EmergencySupport

methods.name: public int getEmfSupport()
methods.comment:
* Provides the NR emergency service fallback support capability as
     * described in 3GPP 24.501 EPS network feature support -> EMF

methods.name: public boolean isVopsSupported()
methods.comment: * Returns whether VoPS is supported by the network

methods.name: public boolean isEmergencyServiceSupported()
methods.comment: * Returns whether emergency service is supported by the network

methods.name: public boolean isEmergencyServiceFallbackSupported()
methods.comment: * Returns whether emergency service fallback is supported by the network

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
